survey_response.review_text: We found Dr. Nagaveni to be the perfect mixture of professionalism and patient friendliness. We only started seeing her in the final month of pregnancy, but she quickly got up to date and prescribed steps to be followed in all aspects including diet, exercise to ensure a smooth delivery. During the delivery itself, She handled everything with calmness and skill, keeping us well informed every step of the way and taking my wife comfort and preferences in mind as much as possible. Thanks to her, my wife was able to deliver our precious, healthy daughter the natural way who has filled our life with joy. Even her team  did a great job, of course ably led by Dr. Nagaveni. We strongly believe that had we consulted Dr. Nagaveni from the beginning of the pregnancy, our experience would have been even smoother. She communicates very clearly and makes you comfortable with any asking any questions or doubts you may have. It was also very obvious that she makes it a point to keep up to date with all latest research in her field and uses all tools at her disposal to benefit of her patients. She is always quick to answer anytime you may need to call her and occasionally when is unable to calls back as soon as she is able to.  There is never any doubt that her patient's best interest is her priority.

Being new in Bangalore, I received Dr Nagaveni’s reference from a neighbor. We had initially met her to take a 2nd opinion as I had faced a subchorionic hemorrhage in my 1st pregnancy.

I have to mention that while Dr Nagaveni’s reviews online are fabulous, she’s even more amazing as a person! While I initially met her to take a 2nd opinion, she remembered the background we discussed on the phone and was equipped to take things forward from there. It didn’t take us long to trust her 100%.

When I encountered an early miscarriage in my 1st pregnancy, Dr Nagaveni stayed very practical when it came to her treatment and left no stone unturned in our journey to becoming parents. She advised only the relevant tests to be taken at the right time, suggested the right weight, exercise and lifestyle changes, etc for both my husband and I, before we conceived again.

As for the 2nd pregnancy, given that I had fibroids, she recommended a scan to assess their position and unlike most doctors, did not suggest surgical removal, as it was not necessary. While the initial trimester was challenging, Dr Nagaveni was instrumental in ensuring all scans and tests were carried out in a timely manner and even checked in periodically between visits to ensure everything was on track. Despite her busy schedule, there is not a single instance where she has not reverted to a message at the end of a busy day.

Dr Nagaveni also took the required precautions and monitored my BP and blood sugar especially during the last trimester when uterine/umbilical artery resistance values were high on scans. Through judicious monitoring, she ensured that this pregnancy was not unnecessarily classified as high risk, which honestly saved us from additional tests, visits, scans and stress.

Till the end, she advocated a natural birth and shared the exercises, diet, etc to prepare for the same. However, on account of fetal distress, we needed a caesarean at the last moment. Even in the OT, she is extremely calm, confident and she and her team make the process seem like a breeze. She is a true expert at putting the patient at ease at this crucial time.

Dr Nagaveni has played a pivotal role in our journey to parenthood and we cannot imagine going through the same without her medical expertise, empathetic nature and positivity. We wholeheartedly recommend her to anyone looking at a highly professional gynecologist and an even better human being to guide them with their pregnancy/medical journey.

By gots grace my wife conceived in immediate next month. From then we continued treatment with her. Kind in her nature, patiance is admirable. She was available 24/7 over phone also for any kind queries and situation. On 7th July we were blessed with Baby boy without any complications to both baby and mother.Thank you Dr. Nagaveni mamRegards,Managala & Naveen Family

"Dear Dr. Nagaveni,

I wanted to take a moment to express my heartfelt gratitude for the exceptional care and expertise you provided during my pregnancy and delivery. Despite the complications that arose, your skill and dedication ensured a successful normal delivery, and I'm thrilled to have welcomed a healthy child.

Your professionalism, compassion, and support made a significant difference in my experience. *** ***** *** *** ** *** **** ******* I've ever encountered, and I feel fortunate to have had you by my side throughout this journey.

I would highly recommend you to others seeking exceptional medical care. Your expertise and caring demeanor make you an outstanding healthcare provider, and I have no doubt that others will benefit from your care just as I did.

Thank you again for your outstanding care and for helping me achieve the birth experience I desired.

First n foremost I wholeheartedly thank Dr. Nagaveni for making me deliver a beautiful girl baby on 22nd July 2024. This is my first pregnancy and from the beginning itself I consulted Dr. Nagaveni for all the monthly check-ups and followed all her instructions and diet. In the 6 month i had faced cervix issue due  to which I underwent cervical cerclage by her only and advised for complete bed rest. Finally with the help of doctor I had normal delivery which I didn't expect also. Thanks to the doctor for supporting me and encouraging me a lot from the starting and mainly during my labour.

Dr. Nagaveni was absolutely amazing throughout the entire process of my wife's delivery. From the moment we met her, she treated us with warmth and professionalism that immediately put us at ease. Her care extended beyond medical expertise; she took care of us like a family member, ensuring we felt supported and informed every step of the way.

One thing that stood out was her responsiveness. Dr. Nagaveni was always available to answer our calls and messages promptly, which was incredibly reassuring during such a pivotal time. Her ability to communicate clearly and compassionately helped alleviate any concerns we had, making the entire experience smoother and less stressful.

During the delivery itself, Dr. Nagaveni's skill and expertise were evident. She handled everything with confidence and precision, ensuring both the health of my wife and the baby were her top priorities. Her calm demeanor and reassuring words were a source of comfort during labor.

Overall, I cannot recommend Dr. Nagaveni highly enough. Her dedication to her patients is exemplary, and her caring approach sets a standard for healthcare professionals. If you're looking for a doctor who not only excels in her field but also genuinely cares for her patients, Dr. Nagaveni is the ideal choice.

Dr. Nagaveni's exceptional care made my entire second pregnancy journey a positive experience. Having been my gynecologist during my first pregnancy as well, I had complete confidence in her expertise. Her kindness and warmth immediately put me at ease, and she patiently answered all my questions, no matter how many I had. Throughout both pregnancies, she genuinely cared about me and strongly advocated a Normal Delivery for me.  Her experience and skills were evident in her consultations and delivery approach.  Even when she switched to Motherhood Hospital, I knew I had to follow her because the quality of care she provided was irreplaceable. Dr. Nagaveni's constant availability throughout both pregnancies was invaluable. I always felt like I was more than just a patient; she truly cared about me and my journey to motherhood. I wholeheartedly recommend Dr. Nagaveni to anyone seeking a compassionate and skilled gynecologist.

Dr. Nagaveni is a very ************* *** approachable gynaecologist who engages patients with empathy, and compassion. During our high-risk pregnancy, she guided us with reassurance and expertise, addressing every concern and question we had. Her dedication and care throughout the pregnancy and delivery were outstanding.

Her ability to explain complex medical information in a clear and understandable way made us feel empowered and informed throughout the process. Her kindness, warmth, and encouragement helped alleviate our anxieties and fears.

Thanks to Dr. Nagaveni's exceptional care, we were blessed with a beautiful and healthy baby girl. We are forever grateful for her expertise, support, and compassion.

We highly recommend Dr. Nagaveni to anyone seeking exceptional gynaecological care especially in high risk pregnancies.

After 32 weeks my complications kept on increasing . My pregnancy journey became more challenging . But it  was doctor assuring voice and positive attitude which helped us kept going . I developed below complication 32 weeks onwards apart from the short cervix length issue which I was already having .
1.Gestational Diabetics .
2.  Severe Polyhydramnious 
3.Cholestasis of pregnancy 
4.Hypertension 
 But doctor always with her smiling face , knowledge and positive attitude gave us hope that for every problem there is a solution . She helped us manage and monitor each and every thing . After 32 weeks I was having itching when I reported to doctor , doctor asked me to do a Blood test . But even before it showed in my report  she with her knowledge and analysis has confirmed that I have cholestasis of pregnancy and she asked to start on low dose of medicine and repeat the blood test after a week . And yes she was correct my bile acid and SGPt and Sgopt was increasing . After that she increased my dose and advice me to repeat the blood test twice a week and do scan once a week and keep a checks on baby movement . She helped manage GD with proper diet and medicine . She monitored my case very closely and always kept a eye on my Reports and everything . After this my platelet count also started decreasing after every week . Earlier she has told us that due to cholestasis and other complications we should be ready for delivery after completing 36 week and she told she will try for normal delivery .This was surprising for me that inspite of so many complications she is telling we can try for normal delivery . But as we know “Man proposes and God disposes .” Around 34 weeks 6 days my bile acid was increasing too much , and so many complications were already there . Doctor recommended us to go for c section at 35 week as it would be risk to wait more . We have full trust and confidence on Doctor so without giving any second thought I got admitted on 26.02.2023 and 27.02.2023 our baby girl arrived . Our “brave girl “ .
